 with the provisioning script","spook start jenkins-agent-01 --headless \\","  --user-data .\/jenkins-agent-setup.sh --provision ssh","","spook start jenkins-agent-02 --headless \\","  --user-data .\/jenkins-agent-setup.sh --provision ssh"]},{"anchor":"Ephemeral-Agents","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Ephemeral Agents"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For clean builds every time, use ephemeral mode. The VM is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"destroyed after the agent disconnects:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start jenkins-agent-01 --headless --ephemeral \\","  --user-data .\/jenkins-agent-setup.sh --provision ssh"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Combine with a cron job or Jenkins pipeline that re-clones","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and re-starts agents between builds."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Running-as-a-Service","text":"Running as a Service","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For persistent agents that survive Mac reboots:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["sudo spook service install jenkins-agent-01","sudo spook service install jenkins-agent-02"],"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Kubernetes-Integration","text":"Kubernetes Integration","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your Jenkins runs on Kubernetes, use the Spooktacular","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Kubernetes operator to manage agents declaratively:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"yaml","code":["apiVersion: spooktacular.app\/v1alpha1","kind: MacOSVM","metadata:","  name: jenkins-agent-01","spec:","  sourceVM: jenkins-base","  cpu: 4","  memoryInGigabytes: 8","  provisioning:","    mode: ssh","    script: |","      #!\/bin\/bash","      curl -sO https:\/\/jenkins.example.com\/jnlpJars\/agent.jar","      java -jar agent.jar -url https:\/\/jenkins.example.com \\","        -secret $AGENT_S